The ipmitool command is a powerful utility for managing and monitoring hardware in a server. It communicates with the Intelligent Platform Management Interface (IPMI) to retrieve server health and status information, including the status of the power supplies.

To check the status of the power supplies using ipmitool, use the following 

sudo ipmitool power supply status

sudo ipmitool sdr type "Power Supply"

sudo ipmitool chassis status

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


The lshw (List Hardware) command is another tool that can help you gather hardware information. It can give you an overview of your system's hardware configuration, including power supply details.

sudo lshw -class power

